SUMMARY
==============================================================================
  bleed@ref-od = clean-vs-OD AMPLITUDE ratio actually present in the output at
  BLEND max-OD / LEVEL noon / DRIVE noon. Negative = clean is quieter than OD.

    tone   L(noon)  taper p  bleed (LEVEL rt)  bleed (BLEND rt)
     110    0.1963    3.446            +5.04dB            -2.32dB
     220    0.2328    2.964            -0.24dB            -1.03dB
     440    0.1785    3.264            +8.99dB            +2.73dB

  Sensitivity of the BLEND-route bleed to L(noon) — the only outside input:
    L(noon)        110Hz        220Hz        440Hz
     0.1500     -4.24dB     -5.33dB     +0.73dB
     0.2000     -2.20dB     -2.51dB     +4.00dB
     0.2300     -1.34dB     -1.14dB     +5.47dB
     0.3000     -0.02dB     +1.35dB     +7.70dB
     0.3711     +0.70dB     +3.06dB     +8.69dB  <- shipped p=1.43

  For comparison, the SHIPPED model (kLevelTaperExp = 1.43) has
  L(noon) = 0.3711, mixing 0.3009*od + 0.1892*clean, i.e. a coefficient
  ratio of -4.03 dB — the handover's '-4.0 dB'. NOTE that figure is the
  COEFFICIENT ratio only; the actual bleed also carries CLEAN_1/OD_1 (drive-dependent).
